<PB REF="037744_0001_100EFCB9193333D0">
<P>ADELAIDE OF WULFINGEN. A TRAGEDY IN FOUR ACTS. (EXEMPLIFYING THE BARBARITY WHICH PREVAILED DURING THE THIRTEENTH CENTURY.)</P>
<P>FROM THE GERMAN OF KOTZEBUE.</P>
<P>NEW-YORK; PRINTED FOR CHARLES SMITH AND S. STEPHENS. 1800</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="dramatis personae">
<PB REF="037744_0002_100EFCBB0CE763F8">
<HEAD>DRAMTIS PERSONAE.</HEAD>
<LIST>
<ITEM><HI>Sir HUGO of Wulfingen,</HI> a knight of the holy cro&s;s again&s;t the Saracens.</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Sir THEOBALD of Wulfingen,</HI> a knight of the holy cro&s;s again&s;t the Pomoranians, and Vandals:&mdash;&s;on of <HI>Sir HUGO.</HI></ITEM>
